<!-- Node: "QuakeCon 2004 is coming!" -->
<div class="body_box_header">QuakeCon 2004 is coming!</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Friday, June 4, 2004 - 19:16</small><br /><br />
The 9th annual QuakeCon video game festival and tournament storms into town August 12-15 at the Gaylord Texan Resort & Convention Center in Grapevine, Texas. This annual fan pilgrimage to the largest, most awe-inspiring North American LAN event will be a four day adrenaline-pumping party with 5,000 of your closest friends.<br />
For additional info visit <a href = "http://www.idsoftware.com">Id Software</a> or head over to <a href = "http://www.quakecon.org/">QuakeCon</a> for all the details.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/comment/reply/287" title="Add a new comment to this page.">Add new comment</a>
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "DOOM Movie" -->
<div class="body_box_header">DOOM Movie</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Friday, June 4, 2004 - 19:02</small><br /><br />
Todd Hollenshead (Id Software CEO) revealed that Warner Brothers, who had the right to the DOOM movie, passed on the option of making it. DOOM's movie license has been picked up by Universal Pictures now. The movie's script is based on DOOM 3, which is as stated by <a href = "http://www.darkhorizons.com/news04/040604d.php">Dark Horizons</a> will be shipped on July 15th.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/comment/reply/286" title="Add a new comment to this page.">Add new comment</a>
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Interplay out of business?" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Interplay out of business?</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Friday, June 4, 2004 - 18:09</small><br /><br />
After Interplay's financial problems, there was a few rumors that their office is closing and they're going out of business.<br />
<br />
<i>Yesterday, <a href = "http://www.gamespot.com">GameSpot</a> talked with the surprisingly affable Caen, who denied the end was nigh for Interplay. His proof? "You can see our stock is trading, so we're still here," said Caen.</i><br />
<br />
So there's still a hope for Kingpin and Fallout fans to see a sequel to their favorite games. Read full article on <a href = "http://www.gamespot.com/news/2004/06/04/news_6099957.html">GameSpot</a>.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/comment/reply/285" title="Add a new comment to this page.">Add new comment</a>
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "SoHL - The Showcase" -->
<div class="body_box_header">SoHL - The Showcase</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/31" title="View user profile.">mazemaster</a> on Thursday, June 3, 2004 - 01:24</small><br /><br />
A new website dedicated to Spirit of HL based mods, maps, and prefabs, <a href="http://showcase.yticodes.net/">SPIRIT - The Showcase</a>, has opened. <a href="http://spirit.valve-erc.com/">SoHL</a> is a Half-Life mod base that includes improved functionality in the same vein as the Lazarus Quake2 mod. Many mods have used SoHL code or used SoHL as a base in the few years since it came out.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/comment/reply/284" title="Add a new comment to this page.">Add new comment</a> &middot; 1 read
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Raven Software is looking for a Technical Artist" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Raven Software is looking for a Technical Artist</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Saturday, May 29, 2004 - 12:54</small><br /><br />
Rick Johnson updated his <a href = "http://finger.planetquake.com/plan.asp?userid=rjohnson&id=16239">GameFinger</a> plan with news that Raven Software is looking for a Technical Artist to work on the Quake 4.<br />
<br />
<b>Technical Artist Position for Quake 4:</b><br />
Raven Software is looking for a Technical Artist for the Quake 4 PC title. We prefer a person with a strong understanding of the technical side of creating art assets, such as creating textures and world models, generating shaders, and proficient in scripting. We also prefer a candidate with strong drawing and painting skills and an ability to model hi and lo-poly models in Maya and/or Lightwave. Programming experience is a plus. A background with Quake 3 shaders, a familiarity with the Quake 3 Editor, and experience in animation and effects are also a definite plus, but not required.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/comment/reply/283" title="Add a new comment to this page.">Add new comment</a> &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/283" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a> &middot; 61 reads
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "DOOM 3 Interview" -->
<div class="body_box_header">DOOM 3 Interview</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2157" title="View user profile.">method</a> on Wednesday, May 26, 2004 - 23:28</small><br /><br />
<a href = "http://www.homelanfed.com/">HomeLAN</a> interviewed Todd Hollenshead, Id Software's CEO, few days ago and disscussed DOOM 3's readyness. The release date is still unknown, but we now that <a href = "http://www.doom3.com/">DOOM 3</a> will be shipped this summer. <a href = "http://www.idsoftware.com/">Id Software</a> seems to be happy with the DOOM 3 outcome and currently they're working on the touch ups. You can read the interview <a href = "http://www.homelanfed.com/index.php?id=23534">here.</a>
